          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"key-insights\">Key Insights</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Cambodia lost 19.3 percentage points of forest cover, the steepest decline in the selection</li>\n<li>China gained 7.3 pp through state-led afforestation, rising from 16.7% to 24.0%</li>\n<li>Costa Rica reversed decades of deforestation through payment-for-ecosystem-services programs</li>\n<li>France quietly expanded its forests by 5.7 pp while tropical nations lost more than 12 pp</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
